==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sweepstakes
<hw>Sweep"stakes`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
winning of all the stakes or prizes; a sweepstake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pos>sing. ⟦or⟧ pl.</pos> <def>The whole money or other
things staked at a horse race, a given sum being put up for each horse,
all of which goes to the winner, or is divided among several, as may be
previously agreed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A race for all the sums staked or prizes
offered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweepwasher</ent>⟦br⟧
